deck: A look-a-like Supergirl from another world
description:
She was a superhero operating on Terra, a world almost identical to Earth but with subtle differences. In a parallel origin to Superman's she was a survivor of an underground civilization which was destroyed. Her father Jaal-Kor, wishing to spare his daughters life, sent her to the surface world in a drilling device, where she gained incredible and became a superhero on Terra. Althought she was the equivalent of Supergirl, bearing many similarities to her, she was the primer superheroe of the world, same as the role Superman has on Earth, including having a secret identity, Leah Lindy and a job as a cub reporter in the Macropolis' Daily Planet.

Her base of operations was the orbiting Fortress of Marvels, and her home city on Terra was Macropolis. Her cousin,Marvel Man, was her partner and secret weapon, in similar fashion to the Silver age Supergirl role.

When Supergirl learned of the existence of Terra, she would go there with Superman's permission to ask Marvel Maid if she can take her place temporarily and see if she can prove to Superman that she can operate as a super hero and not make any mistakes. Marvel Maid agreed, however the subtle differences between Terra and Earth would trip up Supergirl who would in the end still manage to correct her mistakes and save the day. Marvel Man would come to her rescue, when her x-ray vision set an ice berg ablaze, and he would secretly try to assist her while she in turn trained him how to use his powers. He would almost be killed when Supergirl unknowingly turned coal into a diamond to distract a family from spotting them not knowing that it was the one weakness of Marvel Man.

After working together on numerous cases, Supergirl would later ask Might Maid to petition Superman on Earth to allow her to reveal her identity to her adopted planet given her performance on Terra. Marvel Maid agreed, however the subtle differences between Terra and Earth would trip up Supergirl who would in the end still manage to correct her mistakes and save the day.

deck: Mavado was introduced in Mortal Kombat Deadly Alliance as one of the Red Dragon's top officers. In the alternate timeline (Mortal Kombat X), Mavado was working with the Red Dragon for Mileena's rebellion. However, he was killed by Cassie Cage and Jacqui Briggs while trying to kidnap them.
description:
Blood Ties comic

Mavado first appears ambushing Kotal Ketz's army with his Red Dragon army. Later, he's seen watching Kotal Kahn with Sonya Blade and Johnny Cage. He then discovers that the Black Dragon has some valuable hostages (Cassie Cage and Jacqui Briggs), and changes the objectives.

He then finds and ambushes the Black Dragon crew, which happens to be accompanied by Erron Black, and to hold Cassie and Jacqui as hostages. A fight between both factions ensues, with Mavado fighting Kano. Even though Kano tries to tease Mavado with the recent death of a close companion of his, Hsu Hao, Mavado manages to subdue Kano, which makes him flee. Erron Black, who has being left behind, is then severely wounded by Mavado and left to die. Mavado then turns his attention to the girls, who put up a fight. Eventually, Jacqui immobilizes Mavado, and Cassie seizes the opportunity to break one of his legs. She then finishes him, by cutting open his chest. However, the duo is subdued by the remaining Red Dragons and are held hostage.

Sonya Blade and Johnny Cage, who were accompanied by Kotal Kahn's close allies - Reptile and D'vorah - discover Mavado's lifeless body, alongside a barely alive Erron Black, who manages to tell what happened in that moment and what happened to the girls.

deck: Harris Porter as Dragonclaw went through a couple of costumes.
description:
Harris Porter had priors and he had tough time finding work. Things turned worse when his wife left him. Needing to support himself and his daughter, he went to work for Black Cat, but his robbery attempt was stopped by Silk. His first costume ruined, Black Cat sent him to The Repairman, who gave him a new costume. Renaming himself as "Rage" he attacked Silk, but was beaten down again. He told his story to Silk, and she directed him towards Alchemax, since they offered second chances to criminals.

During the time two earth collided, Dragonclaw in his armor helped Silk, who was trapped under a bus.
name: Dragonclaw
